rem) 1000px, (min-width: 78.75rem) 681px, (min-width: 48rem) 450px, (max-width: 48rem) 250px\" height=\"576\" width=\"1024\" decoding=\"\" srcset=\"https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/10541_ALLE-MAND-PA-DAEK_still_05_swe_.png 3840w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/10541_ALLE-MAND-PA-DAEK_still_05_swe_.png?resize=150,84 150w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/10541_ALLE-MAND-PA-DAEK_still_05_swe_.png?resize=300,169 300w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/10541_ALLE-MAND-PA-DAEK_still_05_swe_.png?resize=1024,576 1024w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/10541_ALLE-MAND-PA-DAEK_still_05_swe_.png?resize=1536,864 1536w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/10541_ALLE-MAND-PA-DAEK_still_05_swe_.png?resize=2048,1152 2048w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/10541_ALLE-MAND-PA-DAEK_still_05_swe_.png?resize=178,100 178w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/10541_ALLE-MAND-PA-DAEK_still_05_swe_.png?resize=125,70 125w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/10541_ALLE-MAND-PA-DAEK_still_05_swe_.png?resize=600,338 600w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/10541_ALLE-MAND-PA-DAEK_still_05_swe_.png?resize=660,370 660w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/10541_ALLE-MAND-PA-DAEK_still_05_swe_.png?resize=1280,720 1280w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/10541_ALLE-MAND-PA-DAEK_still_05_swe_.png?resize=1000,563 1000w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/10541_ALLE-MAND-PA-DAEK_still_05_swe_.png?resize=910,511 910w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/10541_ALLE-MAND-PA-DAEK_still_05_swe_.png?resize=681,383 681w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/10541_ALLE-MAND-PA-DAEK_still_05_swe_.png?resize=450,253 450w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/10541_ALLE-MAND-PA-DAEK_still_05_swe_.png?resize=250,140 250w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/10541_ALLE-MAND-PA-DAEK_still_05_swe_.png?resize=296,166 296w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/10541_ALLE-MAND-PA-DAEK_still_05_swe_.png?resize=248,139 248w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/10541_ALLE-MAND-PA-DAEK_still_05_swe_.png?resize=200,112 200w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/10541_ALLE-MAND-PA-DAEK_still_05_swe_.png?resize=270,152 270w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/10541_ALLE-MAND-PA-DAEK_still_05_swe_.png?resize=60,34 60w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/10541_ALLE-MAND-PA-DAEK_still_05_swe_.png?resize=352,198 352w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/10541_ALLE-MAND-PA-DAEK_still_05_swe_.png?resize=110,62 110w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/10541_ALLE-MAND-PA-DAEK_still_05_swe_.png?resize=285,160 285w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/10541_ALLE-MAND-PA-DAEK_still_05_swe_.png?resize=320,180 320w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/10541_ALLE-MAND-PA-DAEK_still_05_swe_.png?resize=640,360 640w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/10541_ALLE-MAND-PA-DAEK_still_05_swe_.png?resize=800,450 800w\"/\u003e\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\n\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\u003cfigcaption\u003e\n\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cspan\u003eFather and son: Filip Hammar (left) with his dad Lars in ‘The Last Journey’\u003c/span\u003e\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003ccite\u003eNexiko\u003c/cite\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\u003c/figcaption\u003e\n\n\t\t\t\n\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\n\tAs the kilometers go by and the companions near the picturesque seaside village of Beaulieu-sur-Mer, Lars’s intrinsic quiet nobility emerges, the way he holds himself to such exacting ethical standards. En route to Beaulieu, they stop at a church where Lars wants to see a priest to get something off his chest – an action he took decades earlier for which he has long felt guilt and shame.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\n\t“When we went to that church for the confession scene — I don’t speak French, and the photographers don’t speak French — we just left them there to film it. We had no idea what they said,” Wikingsson recalls. “Two months later, the editor called me. ‘Do you realize what he’s saying in the confession?’ ‘No, no, no. What does he say?’ ‘Well, he apologizes for being rude to a cab driver in the ‘60s.’ ‘Are you joking?’ It was like such a jackpot in its small way.”\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\n\tThe road trip brought back memories from childhood for Filip — moments he had seen his father show kindness to his students or people in the community.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\n\t“I remember these people — this [immigrant] woman who came from Africa with her son and I remember that she came [to our house] for Christmas,” he said. “Then I realized, ‘Oh, that meant a lot for her [to be invited to Christmas dinner]… I’m happy that I could do [the film] for my dad. Of course, not everyone can [do that], but I think just reminding your parents about how great they’ve been is a good thing to do.”\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n\t\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n\n\t\t\t\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n\t\n\t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?w=300\" data-lazy-src=\"https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"Filip Hammar onstage during the screening of \u0026#39;The Last Journey\u0026#39; at Ross House on December 09, 2024 in Los Angeles, California.\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg 4958w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=150,100 150w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=300,200 300w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=1024,682 1024w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=1536,1022 1536w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=2048,1363 2048w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=630,420 630w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=60,40 60w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=352,234 352w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=900,600 900w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=110,73 110w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=285,190 285w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=320,213 320w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=640,426 640w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=800,532 800w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=1280,852 1280w\" data-lazy-sizes=\"(min-width: 87.5rem) 1000px, (min-width: 78.75rem) 681px, (min-width: 48rem) 450px, (max-width: 48rem) 250px\" height=\"682\" width=\"1024\" decoding=\"\" srcset=\"https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg 4958w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=150,100 150w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=300,200 300w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=1024,682 1024w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=1536,1022 1536w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=2048,1363 2048w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=630,420 630w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=60,40 60w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=352,234 352w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=900,600 900w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=110,73 110w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=285,190 285w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=320,213 320w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=640,426 640w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=800,532 800w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/GettyImages-2189161991.jpg?resize=1280,852 1280w\"/\u003e\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\n\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\u003cfigcaption\u003e\n\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cspan\u003eDirector Filip Hammar at a screening of ‘The Last Journey’ in Los Angeles\u003c/span\u003e\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003ccite\u003eUnique Nicole/Getty Images\u003c/cite\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\u003c/figcaption\u003e\n\n\t\t\t\n\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\n\tHammar continued, “My dad is just a regular guy. There are so many heroes out there like him, and we wanted to make the film epic… as if you’re celebrating [a heroic figure]. When I started talking to people about this film here in the U.S., making a documentary about my dad, everyone was like, ‘What did he do? Who was \u003cem\u003ehe\u003c/em\u003e? Was he the prime minister of Sweden or something?’ And then I said, ‘No, he’s a teacher.’ But he is a very good human being.”\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\n\t\u003cem\u003eThe Last Journey\u003c/em\u003e has been selected as Sweden’s official entry for Best International Feature at the Oscars, and has qualified for Oscar consideration as Best Documentary Feature. It has also become a huge box office hit back home.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\n\t“This started out as a small film. Now, it’s the biggest documentary of all time in Scandinavia,” Hammar shared. “That’s, of course, weird.” \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\n\tClearly, many people are falling in love with Lars Hammar. “It’s like when you see him… he could be anyone,” Filip said. “He represents a lot of good people that are out there.”\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
